00:50:06,720 --> 00:50:10,508
- You know, Daddy didn't
want me to move out here.
- [Bartender] Uh-huh.

695
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:13,797
Ma'am, your bill
comes to $ 2.20.

696
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:16,678
Oh. Uh, okay.
I hope you don't mind...

697
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:19,797
but all I have is a fiifty;
I just came firom my banker's.

698
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:21,711
- That's all right.
- Thank you.

699
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:30,869
Excuse me.
You just moved here?

700
00:50:30,960 --> 00:50:33,952
Yes. Hollywood is,
oh, so exciting.

701
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:35,871
- Isn't it?
- [Giggles]

702
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:38,474
Pleased to make your acquaintance.
I'm Loretta King.

703
00:50:38,560 --> 00:50:40,630
Edward D. Wood,Jr.

704
00:50:40,720 --> 00:50:43,996
- [Bartender] Hi.
Would you like some water?
- No!

705
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:46,435
No water.
No liquids.

706
00:50:46,520 --> 00:50:48,556
I'm terribly
allergic to them.

707
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:53,193
You know, I work in Hollywood.
I'm a producer.

708
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:55,111
Really? Wow!

709
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:57,760
I would love to be
involved in that.

710
00:50:57,840 --> 00:51:00,638
Is that right?
Well, maybe I can help you out.

711
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:03,871
Have you ever thought about
investing in a motion picture?

712
00:51:03,960 --> 00:51:07,919
Perhaps a small amount of money.
How much do your motion pictures cost?

713
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:11,629
Well, my new one, I think,
would be about $60,000.

714
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:15,554
That's all? That seems very reasonable
for an entire picture.

715
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:18,471
[Chuckles]

716
00:51:18,560 --> 00:51:21,358
Would you...
Would you like to, uh...

717
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:24,716
- have a look at the... at the photoplay?
- Oh, sure.

718
00:51:26,760 --> 00:51:28,591
Oh, my.

719
00:51:28,680 --> 00:51:31,035
This is very interesting.

720
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:36,114
Say, do you think it would be possible
for me to maybe play one of these parts?

721
00:51:36,200 --> 00:51:38,998
Oh, you want to be an actress too.
Well, of course.

722
00:51:39,080 --> 00:51:42,834
There's a couple of parts I can think of
right now that you might be perfect for.

723
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:47,436
There's, uh, the secretary in the
newspaper office, the file clerk, um...

724
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:50,034
Hmm. Those sound kind of small.

725
00:51:51,160 --> 00:51:53,833
Here's one that looks good...
Janet Lawton.

726
00:51:55,360 --> 00:51:58,158
I'd sure like to play her.

727
00:51:58,240 --> 00:52:00,196
-Janet Lawton.
- Yes.

728
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:03,078
Janet Lawton is clearly
the part to play.

729
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:08,034
Can't you just see me
in the part?

730
00:52:13,640 --> 00:52:15,471
Yes!

731
00:52:15,560 --> 00:52:17,391
You'd be perfect.

732
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:21,431
You bastard!

733
00:52:21,520 --> 00:52:25,513
You two-timing,
dress-wearing son of a bitch!

734
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:28,398
Honey, it was the only way
I could get the movie made!

735
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:30,311
Who do you think's
been paying the rent?

736
00:52:30,400 --> 00:52:34,154
Who's been helping you type your scripts
and do all your grunt work?

737
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:37,994
- I am sorry!
What did you want me to say?
- You were supposed to say...

738
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:42,073
"No. I wrote that part for
my girlfriend Dolores!"

739
00:52:43,200 --> 00:52:46,590
Snowball, there are
plenty of other parts.

740
00:52:46,680 --> 00:52:49,035
Like what?

741
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:53,160
- The secretary, the file clerk.
- Aaaaah!

742
00:52:53,240 --> 00:52:56,038
You... asshole!

743
00:52:59,120 --> 00:53:02,476
This is gonna be Bela's laboratory,
so it should be real impressive...

744
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:04,869
just like one of those
"Mad Scientist" movies.

745
00:53:04,960 --> 00:53:07,952
I want test tubes, beakers and one
of those electrical things that buzzes.

746
00:53:08,040 --> 00:53:10,838
- You mean a Tesla coil?
- Fine. Whatever. Hop to it!

747
00:53:10,920 --> 00:53:12,751
Right! Right.

748
00:53:14,400 --> 00:53:16,231
- Eddie?
- Yes?

749
00:53:16,320 --> 00:53:19,949
- Which dress do you like better?
- Hmm. I don't know.

750
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:24,272
Say, Bill, which dress works better
for you, the red one or the green one?

751
00:53:24,360 --> 00:53:27,238
- Which one is the red one?
- What do you mean?

752
00:53:27,320 --> 00:53:30,596
I mean, I can't see the difference;
I'm colour blind.

753
00:53:30,680 --> 00:53:32,750
But I kinda like
the dark grey one.

754
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:39,152
At Universal, we used to shoot one
or two scenes a day.

755
00:53:39,240 --> 00:53:42,118
But Eddie can knock off
twenty, thirty.

756
00:53:42,200 --> 00:53:44,839
- He's incredible!
- [Ed] And... action!

757
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:52,196
Okay, you're Dr Eric Vornoff...

758
00:53:52,280 --> 00:53:54,111
and you're upset.

759
00:53:54,200 --> 00:53:58,239
You've worked very hard
on this experiment and you
don't want to see it fail.

760
00:53:58,320 --> 00:54:00,151
N-No, you're not
that upset.

761
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:03,516
You wanna keep moving.
You wanna go through that door.

762
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:08,991
And... cut!
Beautiful.

763
00:54:09,080 --> 00:54:11,674
Print it. Let's move immediately
to scene 52.

764
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:13,591
- Tor, you in place?
- [Tor] Yeah.

765
00:54:13,680 --> 00:54:15,910
- Great. Roll camera!
- Rolling. Slate.

766
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:18,798
- Cue rainstorm.
- [Water Dripping]

767
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:20,711
And... action, Tor.

768
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:26,712
Okay.
You're Lobo.

769
00:54:26,800 --> 00:54:28,631
You're upset.

770
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:32,474
You've worked very hard helping
Dr Vornoff with this experiment.

771
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:35,358
You don't wanna
see it fail.

772
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:37,271
No, no.
You're not that upset.

773
00:54:37,360 --> 00:54:40,193
You wanna keep moving.
You've got to get through that door.

774
00:54:46,040 --> 00:54:47,871
And cut!
Perfect!

775
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:51,236
- Print it. Let's move on.
- Don't you wanna do another take, Ed?

776
00:54:51,320 --> 00:54:54,118
Looks like big baldy had a little
trouble gettin' through the door.

777
00:54:54,200 --> 00:54:56,031
No, it's fine.
It's real.

778
00:54:56,120 --> 00:55:00,159
You know, in actuality, Lobo would have
to struggle with that problem every day.

779
00:55:00,240 --> 00:55:03,994
All right, people, let's get ready.
Actors! I must have my actors!

780
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:08,312
There you are. Loretta, Tor,
I wanna explain this scene;
it's a little complicated, but...

781
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:11,198
- Bela, you'll be sitting there. Okay?
- [Electricity Buzzing]

782
00:55:11,280 --> 00:55:14,078
I'm not getting near
that goddam thing.

783
00:55:14,160 --> 00:55:17,436
- One of them burned me
on The Return Ofi Chandu.
- All right.

784
00:55:17,520 --> 00:55:19,988
- Then you'll be sitting there.
- Good.

785
00:55:20,080 --> 00:55:22,310
Great. All right, gang,
here's the scene.

786
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:25,676
Loretta, you're in a trance; you glide
in and get on the operating table.

787
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:29,036
Now, Tor, you're supposed to tie her
down, but you have an angora fetish...

788
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:32,396
and when you rub that swatch
of angora, it makes you refuse.

789
00:55:32,480 --> 00:55:36,234
So then Bela has to discipline you.
All right? Great! Let's do it!

790
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:39,351
Action!

791
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:46,949
Strap her to the table.

792
00:55:49,440 --> 00:55:51,749
Do as I command you!

793
00:55:53,520 --> 00:55:56,796
- I'll teach you to disobey me!
- Aaaargh!

794
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:58,711
- You will obey!
- Uhhhh!

795
00:55:58,800 --> 00:56:01,268
- Strap her in!
- Uhhhh!

796
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:04,238
Strap her in!
I command you!

797
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:07,118
- Wood! Your cheque bounced.
- I'll get you the money later.

798
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:09,794
- No, I need it now.
- [Bela] I'll teach you to disobey me!

799
00:56:09,880 --> 00:56:11,711
Cut!

800
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:15,156
I am terribly sorry to bother you
while you're shooting...

801
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:18,038
but the guy that owns the stage
needs his money.

802
00:56:18,120 --> 00:56:21,396
Well, then, you should
pay him, shouldn't you?

803
00:56:21,480 --> 00:56:23,789
Yes. Exactly.

804
00:56:29,200 --> 00:56:31,031
I kind of need it now.

805
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:37,390
W-What are you looking at me
like that for?

806
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:40,552
I already gave you
my three hundred.

807
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:42,471
Right.

808
00:56:42,560 --> 00:56:45,154
And now I need
the other sixty thousand.

809
00:56:45,240 --> 00:56:47,834
What other sixty thousand?

810
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:53,474
The other sixty thousand
you said you'd give to me.

811
00:56:53,560 --> 00:56:55,710
You misunderstood, Eddie.

812
00:56:55,800 --> 00:56:59,190
I gave you everything I have in
the world... three hundred dollars.

813
00:57:15,240 --> 00:57:18,073
Well, here we go again.

814
00:57:18,160 --> 00:57:20,469
[Ed] Let me tell ya,
ya can't lose.

815
00:57:20,560 --> 00:57:23,632
It's scary. And if you don't like that,
it's romantic.

816
00:57:23,720 --> 00:57:26,518
Bela Lugosi will portray
Dr Eric Vornoff.

817
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:35,915
And lovely, lovely, lovely
ingenue Loretta King...

818
00:57:36,000 --> 00:57:38,468
is reporter Janet Lawton.

819
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:41,358
- I don't know. Lugosi looks pretty old.
- Huh?

820
00:57:42,880 --> 00:57:44,836
Which role
does Vampira play?

821
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:47,480
Vampira?
Why do you ask?

822
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:49,790
She's standing
right over there.

823
00:57:52,440 --> 00:57:54,829
Well, she plays...

824
00:57:57,040 --> 00:57:59,031
Excuse me one minute.

825
00:58:00,360 --> 00:58:02,476
- [Woman Laughing]
- Pardon me. Miss Vampira?

826
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:05,358
-Yes?
- You don't know me, but I'm Ed Wood.

827
00:58:05,440 --> 00:58:08,716
I'm a film producer and I'm currently in
production on a science fiction piece...

828
00:58:08,800 --> 00:58:10,950
with Bela Lugosi and Swedish
wrestler Tor Johnson.

829
00:58:11,040 --> 00:58:14,032
I don't understand.
Do you want my autograph?

830
00:58:14,120 --> 00:58:16,111
No.

831
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:18,998
No, l... I think my film
is perfect for you.

832
00:58:19,080 --> 00:58:22,834
Want me to show it on my TV programme.
I have nothing to do with that.

833
00:58:22,920 --> 00:58:25,718
- You should call the station
manager at Channel 7.
- No, no. No, no, no, no.

834
00:58:25,800 --> 00:58:29,713
I don't want you to show the movie,
I want you to be in it. Let me explain.

835
00:58:29,800 --> 00:58:32,519
We started shooting, but after
three days we got shut down.

836
00:58:32,600 --> 00:58:35,592
Now we're having a backers party
to raise some more money.

837
00:58:35,680 --> 00:58:38,592
So I thought perhaps you'd like
to come over just to say "howdy"
to some of the backers.

838
00:58:38,680 --> 00:58:41,399
Look, I'm with some friends
and we're about to eat.

839
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:43,311
Please! It would
just take one second.

840
00:58:43,400 --> 00:58:47,029
Come over and meet the backers. There
is a really nice dentist firom Oxnard.

841
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:49,918
Look, buddy, I've got real offers
from real studios.

842
00:58:50,000 --> 00:58:54,198
I don't need to blow some dentist
for a part. Forget it.

843
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:56,350
Miss Vampira!

844
00:58:56,440 --> 00:58:58,829
- Please.
- Ohh! Let's go.

845
00:59:00,280 --> 00:59:03,636
I'm getting a bad feeling about this.
Let's get out of here.

846
00:59:03,720 --> 00:59:05,756
Yeah, I think
you're right.

847
00:59:05,840 --> 00:59:10,072
Thank you, folks, for comin' tonight,
but we better go.

848
00:59:10,160 --> 00:59:13,436
And then Dr Vornoff
falls into the pit...

849
00:59:13,520 --> 00:59:16,671
and his own octopus
attacks and eats him.

850
00:59:16,760 --> 00:59:19,558
- The end.
- Whew!

851
00:59:19,640 --> 00:59:22,154
- Well, that's quite a story.
- Yes.

852
00:59:23,280 --> 00:59:25,874
So, uh, you made the movie...

853
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:28,349
and now you wanna
make it again?

854
00:59:28,440 --> 00:59:30,192
No.

855
00:59:30,280 --> 00:59:34,034
We shot ten minutes of the movie, and
now we're looking for completion funds.

856
00:59:34,120 --> 00:59:36,076
Oh, son, you're too vague.

857
00:59:36,160 --> 00:59:38,958
- [Machine Starting, Whirring]
- Billy Bob!

858
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:42,873
You're cuttin' 'em
too lean.

859
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:45,076
Mr McCoy.

860
00:59:46,440 --> 00:59:49,193
- How can I make you happy?
- [Spits]

861
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:51,953
Okay.

862
00:59:52,040 --> 00:59:53,871
Two things.

863
00:59:53,960 --> 00:59:58,988
Number one: I want the movie
to end with a big explosion.

864
01:00:00,800 --> 01:00:02,711
Sky full of smoke.

865
01:00:04,320 --> 01:00:06,151
Yes.

866
01:00:06,240 --> 01:00:09,198
But it ends with Dr Vornoff
falling into the pit.

867
01:00:09,280 --> 01:00:11,555
Not any more.

868
01:00:11,640 --> 01:00:13,756
Number two.

869
01:00:13,840 --> 01:00:15,956
I got a son.

870
01:00:16,040 --> 01:00:20,431
He's a little slow,
but a good boy.

871
01:00:20,520 --> 01:00:24,399
And somethin' tells me
he'd make a helluva leadin' man.

872
01:00:28,840 --> 01:00:30,671
Sounds perfect.

873
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,592
This is unbelievable.

874
01:00:32,680 --> 01:00:35,478
I woulda bet a million bucks that
Ed wouldn't finish this picture.

875
01:00:35,560 --> 01:00:38,358
Yeah, well, it ain't finished yet, kid;
anything can happen.

876
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:41,231
Stay out of
scratching distance.

877
01:00:41,320 --> 01:00:45,074
- Poodle, you made it. I wasn't
sure you got my message.
- Well, of course I made it.

878
01:00:45,160 --> 01:00:47,958
- Today's the file clerk's big scene.
- That's right.

879
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:50,838
I see the usual gang of misfits
and dope addicts are here.

880
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:53,559
- [Man] Janet, I want you...
- Say, who's the lug?

881
01:00:53,640 --> 01:00:58,509
Str... I want you staying away
from the old Willows place.

882
01:00:58,600 --> 01:01:01,398
Why, that's Tony McCoy. He will be
portraying Lieutenant Dick Craig.

883
01:01:01,480 --> 01:01:03,311
- [Tony Continues Fumbling Lines]
- Really.

884
01:01:03,400 --> 01:01:07,154
- How much money did he put up?
- None. But his dad gave me fifty grand.

885
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:09,549
Hmm. Wood Productions,
the mark of quality.

886
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:12,837
Listen, the movie's getting made;
that's all that matters.

887
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:15,711
- Hello, Harry.
- Oh, hi, Dolores.

888
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:18,109
Oh!
You're Dolores.

889
01:01:18,200 --> 01:01:20,475
I've heard so much about you.

890
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:23,358
I'm Loretta King.
Oh, here, take the chair.

891
01:01:23,440 --> 01:01:25,237
Oh, don't be silly.
Let Harry finish.

892
01:01:25,320 --> 01:01:27,436
You still need
some more work.

893
01:01:27,520 --> 01:01:29,351
No. I'm finished.

894
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:32,716
- All I needed was a touch-up.
- Hmm. That mole still shows.

895
01:01:32,800 --> 01:01:35,758
Uh, ladies!
You both look fine.

896
01:01:36,840 --> 01:01:39,638
Why don't we talk
about the scene?

897
01:01:39,720 --> 01:01:41,756
Okay,Janet Lawton
has just discovered...

898
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:44,149
that Dr Vornoff bought
the old Willows estate...

899
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:47,038
so now she wants to prove that
all the monster stories are true.

900
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:49,156
Well, Eddie,
what's my motivation?

901
01:01:49,240 --> 01:01:52,994
You're the file clerk. You're running
into the next room and bump into Janet.

902
01:01:53,080 --> 01:01:57,790
What is our relationship?
Are we good friends, or is she
just a casual acquaintance?

903
01:01:57,880 --> 01:02:01,236
Dolores, I have five days
to complete this picture.

904
01:02:01,320 --> 01:02:03,151
Don't get goofy on me.

905
01:02:05,280 --> 01:02:07,111
Action!

906
01:02:09,480 --> 01:02:12,119
- Hi,Janet.
- Oh, hi, Marge.

907
01:02:12,200 --> 01:02:14,998
-Janet, still on the monster hunt?
- What do you think?

908
01:02:15,080 --> 01:02:18,356
I think the boss has been
looking for you all day.

909
01:02:18,440 --> 01:02:21,238
Something about the police wanting
those monster stories 86'd.

910
01:02:21,320 --> 01:02:24,278
- You've got the whole town in a panic.
- I can't hear you.

911
01:02:24,360 --> 01:02:28,114
- I said, you've got the who...
- I know what you said,
but I can't hear you.

912
01:02:29,160 --> 01:02:31,469
I get it.
See ya later.

913
01:02:33,120 --> 01:02:36,157
And... cut!
That was perfect.

914
01:02:36,240 --> 01:02:38,879
Of course it was.

915
01:02:38,960 --> 01:02:41,679
Bra-vo!
Bravo!

916
01:02:41,760 --> 01:02:44,558
- Magnifiico.
- Cris, you made it. Thanks a lot.

917
01:02:44,640 --> 01:02:47,438
Naturally. Always happy to help
with a little larceny.

918
01:02:47,520 --> 01:02:49,829
All right, everybody,
that's it for today.

919
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:53,071
The prop crew has a little errand
to run. Paul. Connie.

920
01:03:05,760 --> 01:03:08,558
Darn. I thought they kept this open.

921
01:03:08,640 --> 01:03:10,596
[Tor]
Lobo will fiix.

922
01:03:15,520 --> 01:03:18,080
